quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  66,1,"O Prophet, why do you prohibit what Allah has permitted for you,seeking to please your spouses? Yet Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy."
  66,2,"Allah has already ordained for youpl the dissolution of your oaths, for Allah is your Patron, and He is the All-Knowing, the All-Wise."
  66,3,"And recall when the Prophet confided a matter to some of his spouses, then as soon as one(of them) disclosed it(to another wife) and Allah made it known to him, he communicatedpart of it1 and disregarded another part. Then, when he informed her of it, she said, “Who informed you of this?” He said, “The All-Knowing, the All-Aware informed me.”"
  66,4,"If youdl repent1to Allah, then your hearts have listened. But if both of you band together against him, then Allah is his Patron, as are Gabriel and the righteous believers. And, in addition, the angels will back him."
  66,5,"Perhaps, if he divorces1youpl , his Lord will give him in exchange better spouses than you: Muslim2, believing, devout, repentant, given to worshiping, given to fasting—whether previously married or virgins."
  66,6,"O you who have attained faith, shield yourselves and your families from a fire whose fuel is people and stones; over it are fierce and powerful angels who never disobey Allah in anything He commands them, and they carry out whatever they are commanded."
  66,7,"O you who have denied, make no excuses today; indeed, you are only being repaid for what you used to do."